info.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 03 at 2:23AM PST until January 05 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM WEDNESDAY MORNING THROUGH THURSDAY MORNING... * WHAT...Southeast winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 65 mph possible. * WHERE...Del Norte Interior, Northern Humboldt Coast, Southwestern Humboldt, Northern Humboldt Interior, Southern Humboldt Interior, Mendocino Coast, Northwestern Mendocino Interior, Southwestern Mendocino Interior and Southeastern Mendocino Interior Counties. * WHEN...From Wednesday morning through Thursday morning. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power lines. Widespread power outages are possible. Travel could be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe location prior to the onset of winds.
